CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 30, 1966, pg. 1A, reads: "Pledge Slums Fight Support - At Steelworkers dinner in Pittsburgh honoring I. W. Abel, left to right - Dr. Robert S. Weaver, U. S. secretary of Housing and Urban Development, and Walter Reuther, international president of Auto Workers and vice-president of the AFL-CIO pledge their support human renewal as well as physical renewal in America's cities. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of I. W. Abel, Dr. Robert S. Weaver, and Walter Reuther clasping hands, at Steelworkers dinner
